Assessing the Robustness of Neural System Segregation across Modality, Task & Time

Ethan Knights & Rik Henson

2022-04-25

Notebook: Partial Correlation

Test for effects (Age/Cognition) on SyS that is calculated with partial correlation.

Setup

wd = '/imaging/camcan/sandbox/ek03/projects/functional-segregation_fMRI-MEG/R'; setwd(wd)
library(tidyr)
library(knitr)
library(broom)
library(ggplot2)

Ensure SyS data (.csv) are in the raw directory specified below.
Output images will be stored in the output directory specified below. 

rawDir = 'csv'
outImageDir = 'images'; dir.create(outImageDir,showWarnings = FALSE)

Read dataset.

df = read.csv(file.path(rawDir,'SyS-WithGlobalSignal.csv')); #head(df)

Add Age quadratic term.

df$ageQuad <- poly(df$age,2) #1st linear, 2nd quad

Remove subjects with any missing measure (SyS + Cognition) to simplify age-residualisation later.

df = df[complete.cases(df$Cattell_700), ]
df = df[complete.cases(df$Memory_700), ]
df = df[complete.cases(df$fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm), ]
sprintf('Remaining Subjects = %1.0f',nrow(df))
## [1] "Remaining Subjects = 632"

Create age-residualised SyS + Cognition variables for better plotting.

lm_model <- lm(Cattell_700 ~ age, data = df)
df$Cattell_700_ageResid = residuals(lm_model)

lm_model <- lm(Memory_700 ~ age, data = df)
df$Memory_700_ageResid = residuals(lm_model)

#700
lm_model <- lm(fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm ~ age, data = df)
df$fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm_ageResid = residuals(lm_model)


1) Effect of Age

lm_model <- lm(scale(fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm) ~ scale(ageQuad),
               data = df); summary(lm_model) %>% 
  tidy() %>%  kable(caption = "Table 1. Effect of Age (NoNorm).",col.names = c("Predictor", "B", "SE", "t", "p"),  digits = c(0, 2, 3, 2, 3))
Table 1. Effect of Age (NoNorm).
Predictor B SE t p
(Intercept) 0.00 0.039 0.00 1.000
scale(ageQuad)1 -0.23 0.039 -5.97 0.000
scale(ageQuad)2 -0.10 0.039 -2.63 0.009 

p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = age, y = fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm))
p <- p + geom_point(shape = 21, size = 3, colour = "black", fill = "white", stroke = 2)
#p <- p + stat_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, fill = "grey60", formula = y ~ x, colour = "springgreen3", size = 3)
p <- p + stat_smooth(method = "lm", se = TRUE, fill = "grey60", formula = y ~ poly(x,2, raw = TRUE), colour = "springgreen3", size = 3)
#formatting
p <- p + scale_x_continuous(breaks = round(seq(20, max(80), by = 20),1),limits = c(15,90)) + #ylim(0,400) +
  theme_bw() + theme(panel.border = element_blank(), legend.position = "none",text = element_text(size=14),
                     panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black",size = 1.5),axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "black", size = 1.5))
ggsave(file.path(outImageDir,'Age_fMRI_Partial.png'), width = 25, height = 25, units = 'cm', dpi = 300); p

3) Intraclass correlation between Correlation Approaches

library(irr)
## Loading required package: lpSolve
tmpDF = cbind(df$fMRI_craddock_corr_metric_SyS_chanNorm,df$fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm)
icc(tmpDF)
##  Single Score Intraclass Correlation
## 
##    Model: oneway 
##    Type : consistency 
## 
##    Subjects = 632 
##      Raters = 2 
##      ICC(1) = 0.16
## 
##  F-Test, H0: r0 = 0 ; H1: r0 > 0 
##  F(631,632) = 1.38 , p = 2.56e-05 
## 
##  95%-Confidence Interval for ICC Population Values:
##   0.083 < ICC < 0.235
p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = scale(fMRI_craddock_corr_metric_SyS_chanNorm), y = scale(fMRI_craddock_ridgep_metric_SyS_chanNorm), colour = age))
p <- p + geom_point(shape = 21, size = 3, stroke = 2, alpha = 0.4) + 
  geom_abline(intercept = 0, slope = 1, linetype = 'dashed')
#formatting
p <- p + xlim(-4.8,4) + ylim(-4.8,4) + #Scaled
#p <- p + xlim(0.5,5) + ylim(0.5,5) + #Non-scaled
  scale_color_gradient(low="green", high="red") +
  theme_bw() + theme(panel.border = element_blank(), legend.position = "right",text = element_text(size=14),
                     panel.grid.major = element_blank(), panel.grid.minor = element_blank(), axis.line = element_line(colour = "black",size = 1.5),axis.ticks = element_line(colour = "black", size = 1.5))
ggsave(file.path(outImageDir,"ICC_Correlation-fullVSpartial.png"), width = 25, height = 25, units = 'cm', dpi = 300); p
